<bug>
    <id>16552</id>
    <title>"Unknown filesystem type on /dev/mapper/docker-202" when trying to build image.</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">I'm trying to build a new image from one of my base images, and when build runs, it failed with something like this:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">"'
Step 1 : RUN npm install -g gulp karma-cli mocha coffee-script
Unknown filesystem type on /dev/mapper/docker-202:16-802820-5a81f86e959d602cfe6b7de45f497e59e05b80f0b8817eb780842dea7dd7fabc-init
"'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">I'm on Ubuntu 12.04.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">"'
$ docker version
Client version: 1.7.1
Client API version: 1.19
Go version (client): go1.4.2
Git commit (client): 786b29d
OS/Arch (client): linux/amd64
Server version: 1.7.1
Server API version: 1.19
Go version (server): go1.4.2
Git commit (server): 786b29d
OS/Arch (server): linux/amd64
"'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">I have my '/etc/default/docker' configured to pass '-g /mnt/docker'.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">"'
$ mount | grep '/mnt'
/dev/xvdb on /mnt type ext3 (rw,_netdev)
"'</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">'/dev/xvdb/' is backed by an Amazon EBS.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
